    <p class="text-[14px] md:text-[20px]">I was able to carry out this project during my 10-week internship at the end of my 2nd year at BUT, then once the internship was over the university hired me on a fixed-term contract during the summer vacations to finalize the project. The aim was to create a website to celebrate the 600th anniversary of the University of Franche-Comté. So I was able to take care of the creative part from start to finish. It was the first time I'd managed such a big project, and I gained a lot of experience and skills from it. For the first few weeks, I was in direct contact with the customer, imagining with him the tree structure and the structure of this project with its enormous amount of information: organization was the most important quality to have. Then, once I'd got these ideas out of the customer's head, I was able to start working on the interface and graphics part of the mock-up: my aim was to have a fully prototypable and interactive mock-up, so that no detail would be overlooked and so that I could project myself to the max. In this way, I was able to learn how to develop a professional, interactive system design. Then, after my internship, I was able to create the site on Wordpress. This project introduced me to the world of work, teamwork and the profession of Web Designer.
